To compile:

- Clone the same repo
- Build the docker image in tools/docker with: docker build -t esp-idf .
- docker run -it --rm -w $(pwd) -v /etc/passwd:/etc/passwd -v /etc/shadow:/etc/shadow -u 1000 -v $HOME:$HOME esp-idf make menuconfig
   -> Set toolchain prefix to: xtensa-esp32-elf-

In the docker run:
- /opt/esp/idf/install.sh 
- /opt/esp/idf/export.
- /opt/esp/idf/export.sh 
- make
- docker run -it --rm -w $(pwd) -v /etc/passwd:/etc/passwd -v /etc/shadow:/etc/shadow -u 1000 -v $HOME:$HOME esp-idf make

Don't turn on C++ exception, that uses up too many sections in the image.

Apply the patch xTimerAbortDelay.patch to the SDK.

Using the Led disables UART Tx (and printf..)
